{{wikipedia}}

====Alternative spellings====
'''travelling-salesman problem''' (''Commonwealth English''), '''traveling salesman problem''' (''US English''), '''traveling-salesman problem''' (''US English'')

#(''mathematics'') The problem in [[combinatorial]] [[optimization]] in which, given a number of cities and the costs of travelling from one to the other, it is required to determine the cheapest route that visits each city once and then returns to the initial city.

